			<section>
									<div class="summary">
						<p>Writes rows of columns.</p>
					</div>
				
									<div class="description">
						<p>This method expects asceding integer values as the keys, which map to the appropriate
columns. Currently, there is no special "header" option, but you can define them for your
own.</p>
<p>Example Usage:</p>
<pre><code class="language-php">$output = [
    ['Name', 'Age'],
    ['----', '---'],
];
foreach($users as $user) {
    $output[] = [$user-&gt;name, $user-&gt;age];
}
$this-&gt;columns($output);
</code></pre>
<p>Would render something similar to:</p>
<pre><code class="language-php">Name       Age
----       ---
Jane Doe   22
Foo Bar    18
</code></pre>
<p>This method also calculates the needed space between the columns. All option params given
also get passed down to the <code>out()</code> method, which allow custom formatting. Passing something
like <code>$this-&gt;columns($output, ['style' =&gt; 'red]</code> would print the table in red.</p>
					</div>
							</section>

